<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - GAUGES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>GAUGES</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>All of the gauges can be removed without removing the gauge cluster.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removing Electronic Gauges</title>
            <figure id="f0824511" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0824511.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Electronic Gauge Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PIN CONNECTOR (2 OR 3 PLACES)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRIC GAUGE (TYPICAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GAUGE CLUSTER (LEFT)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the screw in the cluster corners and remove the cluster bezel plate (
                        <hotlnk document="s08245x_14.xml" xrefid="f0824505">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Grasp gauge by the edge and pull straight out (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0824511">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installing Electronic Gauges</title>
            <para>The identity and placement of the gauge is on a label at the bottom of the cluster.</para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Align the gauge with the connector pins and push it onto the pins.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Position cluster bezel plate and tighten screws.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removing Mechanical Gauges</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not disconnect the air line tube nuts from the socket fittings. This will dump the
                        compressed air. See Removing Gauge Clusters, for proper socket fitting removal.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0824512" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0824512.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Mechanical Gauge Removal (Rotate)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GAUGE CLUSTER (RIGHT HAND SHOWN)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MECHANICAL PRESSURE GAUGE, QUICK DISCONNECT TYPE (AIR PRESSURE SHOWN)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0824513" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G0824513.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Mechanical Gauge Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. QUICK DISCONNECT TIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. QUICK DISCONNECT SOCKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SCHRADER VALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BAYONET LOCK GROOVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BAYONET LOCK LUG (BOTH SIDES)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. GAUGE CLUSTER (LEFT HAND, REFERENCE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. MECHANICAL PRESSURE GAUGE (OIL PRESSURE SHOWN)</callout1>
                    <callout1></callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove the screw in the cluster corners and remove the cluster bezel plate (
                        <hotlnk document="s08245x_14.xml" xrefid="f0824505">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Grasp the gauge by the edge, lifting up slightly on the bottom and swinging the bottom of the
                        gauge toward the center of the gauge cluster (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0824512">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the gauge has been swung 20 degrees, it can be pulled straight out. When the gauge has
                        been swung that far, the bayonet lugs will stop it (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0824513">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Forcing the gauge past the bayonet lugs can cause breakage of the bayonet lugs.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installing Mechanical Gauges</title>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Insert the gauge quick connect tip into the quick connect socket, aligning the bayonet,
                        pushing in and turning until the locking tab snaps into place. The gauge is started 20 degrees
                        out of position (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0824512">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When the gauge is swung into place, a plastic lock tab in the cluster will snap into a groove
                        in the gauge housing and locate the gauge in the proper position (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0824513">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Position cluster bezel plate and tighten screws.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
